SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYSunday 1 May S10 V3 Arsenal continue their push for Champions League Kaye with a tough derby against West Ham, who have their own hopes of returning to European club competition next season. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Glasgow Celtic vs Glasgow Rangers: Third Old Firm derby in a month after Celtic won at Ibrox to strengthen their league le ad but the lost in extra time at Hampden in the Scottish Cup semi-final.M2 Elche vs Osasuna: Elche are looking for a third La Liga win in a row. Osasuna had an upset win at Valencia in their last away assignment.M3 Go Ahead Eagles vs Vitesse Arnhem: Vitesse are unbeaten on seven past trips to Deventer with two draws and five victoriesM4 Empoli vs Torino: Empoli are defending an unbeaten home record against Torino with five victories and seven draws in 12 past visits.M5 Everton vs Chelsea: Everton manager Frank Lampard is up against his old club as the Toffees try to keep up their top Premier League status. Chelsea have lost on their previous three visits to Goodison Park.M6 Lorient vs Stade Reims: Lorient are not yet out of Ligue 1 relegation danger. They have five wins in their past six clashes with Reims, drawing the last encounter earlier this season.M7 Tottenham Hotspur vs Leicester City: One point in their past two games has stymied Spurs’ Champions League hopes. Leicester’s last two league outings have both ended in draws.M8 Granada vs Celta Vigo: Granada are looking to fight their way out of the La Liga relegation zone. Celta have lost three of their previous four matches.M9 FC Basel v FC Zurich: Zurich will be crowned Swiss champions for the first time since 2007 if they avoid defeat against their closest challengers.M10 West Ham United vs Arsenal: Arsenal are unbeaten in their past five clashes against the Hammers, winning four of them. Suggested permutation: R128.00 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 1,2 x 3 x 2,3 x 1 x 1,2 x 2,3 x 2,3